 ```
 
+Git wrapper progress on stdout does NOT leak into generated script.
+
+A git wrapper on PATH may write progress to stdout even with `--quiet`. That text
+must not contaminate the generated plugin script output.
+
+```zsh
+% function git { mockgit "$@"; print "GIT_PROGRESS_NOISE: some progress text" >&1; }
+% local script_output
+% script_output=$(antidote-script --kind clone baz/qux 2>/dev/null)
+% print -l "$script_output" | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+fpath+=( "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/baz/qux" )
+source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/baz/qux/qux.plugin.zsh"
+% [[ "$script_output" != *"GIT_PROGRESS_NOISE"* ]]
+%
+% function git { mockgit "$@" }
+%
+```
+
